Betting Control and Licensing Board director Simon Chelugui has ditched his bid for Baringo governor. He will run for senator instead.Chelugui will run on the Jubilee Party ticket.The governor race is now a three-horse between Baringo Knut secretary general Stanley Kiptis, former Kenya School of Government Kabarnet campus director Isaac Chebon and incumbent Benjamin Cheboi.Sources say Chelugui&rsquo;s shift was decided after a meeting among Jubilee leaders from the Rift during the Christmas holiday at Deputy President William Ruto&rsquo;s Sugoi home.&ldquo;They saw Chelugui as a powerful equal able to smash down the political heavyweight Senator Moi,&rdquo; Barwessa ward MCA Joseph Makilap told the Star last Wednesday.